# Merge strategies for files where parallel branches frequently both add entries.
#
# `merge=union` keeps both sides' lines when both branches modified the same file,
# instead of producing conflict markers. This is safe for *append-only* checklists
# where the order of entries is not semantically significant. Do NOT use it for
# files where ordering matters (e.g. registry arrays in Swift) or where duplicate
# rows would corrupt structure (JSON/YAML/tabular Markdown).
#
# Caveat: if two branches mark the same checklist item, both lines will be kept
# and you may end up with a duplicate entry. Hand-fix during review when this
# happens — it is rare and trivial compared to the textual conflicts it prevents.

